properties.Title: Heat Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: An extended period of very warm to hot weather is expected. Time span: continuing into Friday and possibly Saturday. Maximum daytime temperatures: 30 to 35 degrees Celsius (Humidex 36 to 39) on Thursday and Friday. Cooler conditions are expected along parts of the coast. Minimum overnight temperatures: 18 to 21 degrees Celsius. Locations: New Brunswick. Remarks: Very high temperatures will dominate over New Brunswick for the next several days. The warmest conditions are expected to occur over most areas on Thursday and Friday with cooler temperatures over northeastern parts of the province on Saturday. ### Extreme heat affects everyone. Heat warnings are issued when very high temperature or humidity conditions are expected to pose an elevated risk of heat illnesses, such as heat stroke or heat exhaustion. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NBstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NBStorm.

properties.Summary:
